API Audit Log – S27
Author: Jasmine
===========================================


SECTION 1: BOLA VULNERABILITY (ID SWAP)
-------------------------------------------
Original request:
GET /api/v1/profile/101

Modified request:
GET /api/v1/profile/102

Leaked secret from the CISO profile:
admin_secret: CISO-KEY-9981

Explanation:
The API lets anyone change the ID number in the URL and access another user’s profile. There is no authorization check, which makes this a BOLA (Broken Object Level Authorization) vulnerability.


SECTION 2: BUSINESS LOGIC FLAW (DISCOUNT BRUTE FORCE)
-------------------------------------------
Captured request body:
{"discount_code": "0000"}

Intruder attack range:
9900 → 9999

Successful discount code:
9999

Server response:
"discount": "100% OFF"

Explanation:
The API accepts any 4‑digit code and does not limit attempts. Because there is no rate limiting or server-side validation, the discount code can be brute‑forced easily.


SECTION 3: RECOMMENDATIONS
-------------------------------------------
- Add authorization checks so users can only access their own profile.
- Use non-sequential, random identifiers instead of predictable numbers.
- Add rate limiting to stop brute-force attacks.
- Validate discount codes on the server side.
- Log repeated failed attempts and alert admins.
- Never trust user-controlled input in URLs or request bodies.


